# Output conventions

**Save all outputs as a markdown report**

---

## 1. Summary table

Show a full code table at the top of the document, sorted by frequency (descending):

| Code | Definition | # Quotes |  
|------|------------|----------| 
| code_name | brief noun phrase (≤10 words) | N |  

---

## 2. Per-code sections

Create a `<details>` foldable block for each code:

```
<details>
<summary>**Code Name** (N quotes)</summary>

...quotes...

</details>
```

---

## 3. Quotes within each section

- Display each quote as a blockquote with an interviewee ID label:

  > "Quote text here."
  > — P01

- If a quote is assigned more than one code, flag it inline:
  `[MULTI-CODE: Code A, Code B]`

  Example:

  > "Quote text here." `[MULTI-CODE: Survey Goals, Validation]`
  > — P03

---

## 4. Definitions

Keep code definitions to a brief noun phrase (≤10 words). Avoid full sentences.
